Class SeriesReport

  • java.lang.Object
    • test.SeriesReport
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class SeriesReport
extends Object
implements Serializable
    Test series report.

    This class contains three lists: a list of tests that succeeded, a list of tests that were not run, and a list of reports from tests that failed. Tests not run are so because prerequisite tests did not complete successfully, or were not run at all.

    See Also:

        public boolean successful()
        Returns true if and only if the test series completed successfully.

        The test series is considered to have completed successfully if all tests have been run, and no tests failed.
